==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Star of David
<hw>Star" of Dav"id</hw>. <def>A symbol consisting of two overlapped
equilateral triangles forming a star with six points, used as a symbol
of Judaism. It is also called <altname>Magen David</altname>,
<altname>Mogen David</altname>, and <altname>Shield of David</altname>,
and is shaped identically to the <er>hexagram</er> and <er>Solomon's
seal</er>. It is used on the flag of the modern state of
Israel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

